# Python Dependencies

## 1. Source of Truth

- **`pyproject.toml`** declares project metadata, dependencies, and tool configuration (**ruff**, **pyright**, **pytest**).
- **`uv.lock`** pins transitive versions for reproducible builds.

## 2. Adding Dependencies

```bash
uv add <package>
uv add --dev <dev-only-package>
```

## 3. Lockfile

After changing dependencies:

```bash
uv lock
```

Commit **`uv.lock`** when the project tracks it.

## 4. Syncing Environments

```bash
uv sync
```

Use **`uv run <command>`** to execute tools and scripts inside the project environment.

## 5. Constraints

- Do not mix ad-hoc **`pip install`** instructions into CI or docs—use **`uv`** so the lockfile stays authoritative.
